The Proposal: -

Buldhana district. januna, T. The original budget of the Khamgaon Tap Water Supply Scheme was prepared by the CEO, Zilla Parishad, Buldana vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2.

Also, Reference No. 1 under Rs. The price of 1,77,236, 900 / - is admin approved. 9 and Reference No. 5 of the Department. Post facto approval has been granted to the bid for the additional rate of the scheme vide letter dated 15.02.2022. The Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Buldana has proposed to give revised administrative approval to the proposed tap water supply scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here. 8.11.2023 and d. The letter dated 22.12.2023 has been submitted to the government. Reference No. 3 here. Under the letter dated 08.05.2024, the government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price which would be in accordance with the revised technical approval given by the Superintending Engineer, Maharashtra Life Authority Board, Akola.
The government's decision:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Dr. Januna Ta. The scheme of Khamgaon Tap Water Supply Scheme has been sanctioned at an additional cost of Rs. 1 crore, subject to the following conditions, namely, acceptance of tender at higher rates, increase in the cost of the scheme due to Goods and Services Tax (GST rate hike) and technical changes. The revised price of 2,17,50, 230 / - (Rupees Two Crore Seventy Lakh Fifty Thousand Two Hundred and Thirty Only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Supra 2024 / Q2 / UT 23 (E Office 20.761585)
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval as well as the original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred every year for implementation, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), reduction in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) A CAG report in 2013 shows that 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity bills. Hence, in order to make the scheme financially viable, it will be the responsibility of the concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad to increase the water tariff as per requirement.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.

2. Schemes for which tenders have been floated. The increased cost of the revised cost of the scheme, which has already been approved, should be met from the sanctioned grant of the Jal Jeevan Mission programme only.

as well as the plans. The Discovered / Approved Cost concept is applicable to schemes with 21.06.2022 and subsequent work orders. Government approval should not be taken into account in case of tender proceedings and territorial decisions or irregularities. Therefore, if such a case arises, the relevant enforcement mechanism will be solely responsible for it.

4. Revised administrative approval to the proposed scheme is provided by the Department of Finance. The Government Decision No. 2013 / Q. No. 30/2013 Regulations, Part II, Part I, Sub-section III, No.
